Jenna Etheridge, News24Mandrax bust in Belhar. (Saps, Supplied) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town &ndash; Officers have seized 32 000 Mandrax tablets in Belhar, Western Cape police said on Thursday.The tablets, discovered on Wednesday morning, had an estimated street value of R960 000, said police spokesperson Lieutenant Colonel Andr&eacute; Traut.He said two suspects, aged 28 and 48, were arrested and would appear in court once charged.The bust was made during Operation Fiela in the area, according to the SA Police Service Twitter Account.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.